          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "El Ride",
                  "textSize": "heading-three"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Diana L. Montejano",
                  "textSize": "heading-four"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "(From “Paginas de Mi Vida)",
                  "textSize": "heading-four"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "I got on el #68 everyday for who knows how long,"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "traveling down Guadalupe Street to visit my father"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "at La Juvenil, y mi primo Isaac en la esquina,"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "at Project Stay, above el Progresso Drugstore, en"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "la misma cuadra que el Victory Temple where I went"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "to cry when my grandmother died. Si, #68 took me"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "all the way to the Brown Berets Headquarters, y pa’"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "la marcha protesting police brutality, al parade del"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Diez y seis, Ray's Drive-Inn, pa' watchar mi camarada"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Devil, cercas Segovia's dulcería.  Yeah, I rode that"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "sometimes, air-conditioned, over-crowded, siempre sweaty"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "smelling body-pusher down la Guada, with la puta Meche,"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "winos, junkies, paint-sniffers, grandmas, grandpas, con"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "mi comadre Chelo y sus hüercos malitos, and the working"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "people too.  Pos, I rode with them, whistling"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "the Rosa and Buster Buppet jingle from los cartoon"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "commercials promoting mass transit for a quarter,"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "It’s also easy when you ride the bus!",
                  "italic": true
                },
                {
                  "text": " waiting and"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "waiting por el #68, mi aventón to the next conexión."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
